The same die was later used for Reverse B on the 1803 JR-2 dime. The cracks, enlarged and multiplied, now run 1) from I2, C and A3 to the rim;
                  2) from cloud 6 through the stars, shield, left claw and arrows to the rim; 3) from the rim to the top of F and the right wing; and in a late
                  die state 4) from the rim at D through the stars to S2 and the rim.
